In 2016, the government of Uzbekistan passed a law that allows women to have up to 12 weeks of paid maternity leave. However, the law does not provide paid paternity leave, and the government does not provide any paid leave for fathers. The law also does not provide paid leave for women who have miscarriages or stillbirths.

The government of Uzbekistan has made some progress in improving maternal health. In 2016, the government launched a program to provide free prenatal care to all pregnant women. The program also provides free prenatal vitamins and supplements to pregnant women.
